{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place scallopini onto a clean work surface. Place 3-4 basil leaves onto each scallopini. Roll each stick of mozzarella in a piece of pancetta tucking in edges to seal in cheese. Place a cheese parcel onto bottom edge of each scallopini and roll up tightly to enclose filling. Secure with a toothpick and place seam-side down into Varoma dish and tray. Season with salt and pepper and set aside.","Place garlic and onion into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 6<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add oil and sauté <b>2 min\/120°C\/speed 2<b>.","Add pesto, passata, salt and pepper. Place Varoma with involtini into position, secure Varoma lid and cook <b>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>.","Add asparagus into Varoma around involtini. Secure Varoma lid and cook <b>5-7 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>, until involtini are still sightly pink inside and the asparagus are tender. Carefully remove toothpicks from involtini. Serve involtini with tomato sauce and asparagus."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["8 pieces veal scallopini (see Tips)","2 - 3 sprigs fresh basil, leaves only","100 g fresh mozzarella, cut into 8 sticks (approx. 1 x 5 cm)","8 slices pancetta","½ tsp salt, plus extra to season","2 pinches ground black pepper, plus extra to season","2 garlic cloves","150 g brown onion, cut into quarters","20 g olive oil","50 g sun-dried tomato pesto (see Tips)","500 g tomato passata","2 bunches asparagus, trimmed"]}],"id":"r254172","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-0UmVo89EYXs\/XZQGZ5Fvd-I\/AAAAAAAAb9s\/AdJzHc7aNkw9VyTDbhNQU2GYoRxUE2faQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_PHeST8nFlyxVfTJZ.png","title":"Veal involtini","publishedAt":"2018-10-15T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"112.9 g","fat":"29.2 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"8.8 g","calories":"3187.5 kJ \/ 758.9 kcal"},"usefulItems":"tooth picks","hintsAndTricks":["Ask your butcher to prepare your scallopini for you. Make sure your scallopini is thin (approx. 3 mm in thickness), otherwise cooking time may vary. Girello, a cut of beef, can replace veal in this recipe.","To make your own pesto, please refer to the recipe in <i>The Basic Cookbook<\/i>.","For a heartier meal, add other quick-cooking vegetables to the Varoma when adding asparagus (such as green peas, snow peas or thinly sliced potatoes)."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","35m","4 portions"]}